  out_height: 30%
---

When the dataset is split to a training and a test set, it can be relevant to check that the two 
sets share the same space. From a PCA, this can be done by plotting the score vs. orthogonal 
distances (SD and OD, respectively). This can be implemented for instance by using function `occsdod` 
that also returns a one-class classification (OCC) index as a compromise between SD and OD. 


```julia
using Jchemo, JchemoData
using JLD2, CairoMakie
```

#### Import data

```julia
using JchemoData, JLD2, CairoMakie
path_jdat = dirname(dirname(pathof(JchemoData)))
db = joinpath(path_jdat, "data/cassav.jld2")
@load db dat
@names dat
```

```julia
X = dat.X
@head X
```

```julia
Y = dat.Y
@head Y
```

```julia
year = Y.year 
tab(year)
```

#### Split Tot to Train/Test

```julia
s = year .<= 2012
Xtrain = X[s, :] 
Xtest = rmrow(X, s) 
ntot = nro(X) 
ntrain = nro(Xtrain) 
ntest = nro(Xtest)
(ntot = ntot, ntrain, ntest)
```

#### Model fit and scores T

Preliminary PCA model fit on the training set to compute the scores T and the loadings P
that will be used in the SD-OD space computation.

```julia
model0 = pcasvd(nlv = 10) 
fit!(model0, Xtrain)  
fitm0 = model0.fitm 
@names fitm0
```
#### SD-OD space

**OCC model fit** 

```julia
model = occsdod()
fit!(model, fitm0, Xtrain)
fitm = model.fitm ;
@names fitm
@head dtrain = fitm.d
```

**Prediction on test** 

```julia
res = predict(model, Xtest)
@names res
@head dtest = res.d
```

**Final graphs** 

```julia 
d = vcat(dtrain, dtest)
group = [repeat(["Train"], ntrain); repeat(["Test"], ntest)]
color = [:purple, (:red, .3)]
f, ax = plotxy(1:length(d.dstand), d.dstand, group; color = color, size = (500, 300), leg_title = "Type of obs.", 
  title = "SD-OD", xlabel = "Observation index", ylabel = "Standardized distance")
hlines!(ax, 1; linestyle = :dot)
f
```

```julia 
s = dtrain.d .> fitm.cutoff
a = fitm.coefs[1]
b = fitm.coefs[2]
f, ax = plotxy(dtrain.sdsigma, dtrain.odsigma; color = (:red, .3), xlabel = "SD / sigma", ylabel = "OD / sigma")
scatter!(ax, dtest.sdsigma, dtest.odsigma; color = :purple, label = "Test")
ablines!(ax, a, b; linewidth = .7, linestyle = :dash)
axislegend(ax; position = :rb)
f
```

